template<typename C , typename B , typename IT , typename O_IT , typename S >
O_IT geometry::impl::intersection::clip_linestring_with_box ( const B &  b,
IT  begin,
IT  end,
O_IT  out,
const S &  strategy 
)

Clips a linestring, or pair of iterators, with a box.

A linestring, defined by an iterator pair, is intersected (clipped) by the specified box and the resulting linestring, or pieces of linestrings, are sent to the specified output operator.

Template parameters:
  • C container type, for example a vector of points, matching the output-iterator type, the points should also match the input-iterator type
  • B box type
  • IT in iterator type
  • O_IT output iterator type, which outputs linestrings
  • S strategy, a clipping strategy which should implement the methods "clip_segment" and "add"
